---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
---

<DocsLayout title="Webhooks">
  <h1>Webhooks</h1>
  <p>
    EncodeSwarmr can send notifications to external services when events occur. Webhooks support Discord, Microsoft Teams, and Slack with HMAC-SHA256 signature verification.
  </p>

  <h2>Supported Providers</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Provider</th><th>Format</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td>Discord</td><td>Discord webhook embeds</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Microsoft Teams</td><td>Adaptive Cards</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Slack</td><td>Block Kit messages</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Configuration</h2>
  <p>Add webhooks to your <code>controller.yaml</code>:</p>
  <pre><code>webhooks:
  - name: discord-alerts
    url: https://discord.com/api/webhooks/123/abc
    provider: discord
    secret: my-hmac-secret
    events:
      - job.completed
      - job.failed
      - agent.offline
  - name: slack-ops
    url: https://hooks.slack.com/services/T.../B.../xxx
    provider: slack
    secret: another-secret
    events:
      - job.failed
      - agent.offline</code></pre>

  <h2>Available Events</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Event</th><th>Description</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>job.queued</code></td><td>A new job has been added to the queue</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>job.started</code></td><td>An agent has started processing a job</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>job.completed</code></td><td>A job finished successfully</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>job.failed</code></td><td>A job failed after all retries</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>agent.online</code></td><td>An agent connected to the Controller</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>agent.offline</code></td><td>An agent lost connectivity</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>analysis.completed</code></td><td>Source analysis finished</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Signature Verification</h2>
  <p>
    Each webhook delivery includes an <code>X-EncodeSwarmr-Signature</code> header containing an HMAC-SHA256 signature of the request body using your configured secret. Verify this signature on the receiving end to ensure authenticity.
  </p>
  <pre><code># Signature format:
# X-EncodeSwarmr-Signature: sha256=&lt;hex-encoded-hmac&gt;

# Verification pseudocode:
expected = hmac_sha256(secret, request_body)
assert signature == "sha256=" + hex(expected)</code></pre>

  <h2>Retry Delivery</h2>
  <p>
    Failed webhook deliveries are retried with exponential backoff. The retry schedule:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>1st retry: 30 seconds</li>
    <li>2nd retry: 2 minutes</li>
    <li>3rd retry: 10 minutes</li>
    <li>4th retry: 1 hour</li>
    <li>After 4 failures, the delivery is marked as failed</li>
  </ul>

